title: Chelsea vs Liverpool - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 35
description: Chelsea are winless in their last 10 meetings with Liverpool in all competitions, only once before going longer without a win over the Reds. After their 2-1 win in October, Liverpool are looking to complete their first league double over Chelsea since their title-winning 2019-20 campaign. Arne Slot could become only the third Reds boss to win both of his first two league games against Chelsea in charge of the club, after Bill Shankly and Roy Evans.

title: EPL Stories 2024/25 - Andy Carroll
description: PL Stories follows the Journey of Andy Carroll, from his high- flying Premier League days to his latest chapter in Bordeaux. The documentary captures Carrolls resilience in navigating the various challenges of his football career, reflecting on the ups and downs along the way. We Join him In Bordeaux where he looks back on his colourful career while leaving us in no doubt about his drive to prove himself once again.

title: Arsenal vs AFC Bournemouth - English Premier League 2024/25 Week 35

Bournemouth have kept just one clean sheet in their 15 Premier League meetings with Arsenal, though it was a 2-0 victory in the reverse fixture this season.

title: Real Sociedad vs Osasuna - LaLiga 2024/2025 Week 11
description: Real Sociedad have only lost one of their last 16 matches against Osasuna in LaLiga, losing 0-1 in February 2024 in their last league meeting. They have not lost back-to-back matches against Osasuna in the competition since September 2010. Following their victory at the Reale Arena in February 2024, Osasuna have the chance to win on two successive visits to Real Sociedad for the first time in the history of LaLiga.

title: LaLiga Highlights - Week 11
Real Madrid vs Barcelona - LaLiga 2024/2025 Week 11

Since 2020, FC Barcelona have lost 10 of their 14 games in El Clásico in all competitions. This is as many defeats as they suffered in the previous 39 such games, dating back to Josep Guardiolas first match as coach in December 2008.

title: Leganes vs Celta de Vigo - LaLiga 2024/2025 Week 11

Only against Espanyol have they achieved more wins in the competition. After winning their first two visits in all competitions, 2-1 in Copa del Rey in 2001 and 2-0 in LaLiga in 2017, Celta de Vigo have not won in any of their last three away games against CD Leganes.

It’s been a very tight race to receive this accolade, and this feature will underline the important role this goalkeeper has played in his team, with stats to explain the reasons behind his success. We will also look back at his best saves and interventions.

In fact, they have scored on each of their last three visits to Pucela, after failing to do so on nine of their previous 10 league trips.

A strong qualifying position often correlates to race success — and Moto2 margins are the slimmest in racing.
